        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 6 at 9:00PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 859 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Kit Carson, or 27 miles west of Cheyenne Wells, moving southeast at
40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Sheridan Lake, Chivington, and Brandon.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
